# Text Field

A single-line text input for short, free-form values.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-54")], [
      field.label([attribute.for("intro-email")], [html.text("Email")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("intro-email"),
        attribute.type_("email"),
        attribute.value("ada@glow.dev"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-54")], [
      field.label([attribute.for("intro-api-key")], [html.text("API Key")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("intro-api-key"),
        attribute.type_("password"),
        attribute.value("••••••••••••"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add text_field
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical()], [
    field.label([attribute.for("email")], [html.text("Email")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("email"),
      attribute.placeholder("ada@glow.dev"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Set the state of a text field with standard attributes, or compose it with field helpers.

### Default

A bare text input inside a field, with placeholder copy.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("project-name")], [html.text("Project Name")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("project-name"),
      attribute.placeholder("my-glow-app"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Required

Pass the required attribute and the field's label surfaces an accent asterisk.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("workspace-name")], [
      html.text("Workspace Name"),
    ]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("workspace-name"),
      attribute.placeholder("acme-rocketry"),
      attribute.required(True),
    ]),
    field.description([], [html.text("Used in your workspace URL.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Invalid

Set aria-invalid to surface the destructive border. Pair with field.error for the message.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("webhook-url")], [html.text("Webhook URL")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("webhook-url"),
      attribute.aria_invalid("true"),
      attribute.value("not-a-url"),
    ]),
    field.error([], [html.text("Must be a valid HTTPS URL.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Disabled

Add the disabled attribute to lock a field and drop it from the tab order.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("workspace-id")], [html.text("Workspace ID")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("workspace-id"),
      attribute.value("ws_8d4f1a2c"),
      attribute.disabled(True),
    ]),
    field.description([], [html.text("Generated on workspace creation.")]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Elements

A single input control, no children. Type, value, and validation state all come from the attributes you pass in.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `text_field.input(attrs)` | Standalone text input. Renders a native input element. |

### Attributes

Standard Lustre attributes and events the text field responds to. Pass them through the attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.type_(...)` | Native input type: "text", "email", "password", etc. |
| `attribute.value(...)` | Controlled value. Pair with event.on_input to handle keystrokes. |
| `event.on_input(...)` | Message dispatched on every keystroke with the current value. |
| `attribute.placeholder(...)` | Placeholder text shown when the value is empty. |
| `attribute.aria_invalid("true")` | Surfaces the validation state: destructive border and error ring. |
| `attribute.required(True)` | Marks the input as required; field.label surfaces an indicator. |
| `attribute.disabled(True)` | Locks the input, blocks pointer events, and reduces opacity. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the input's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="text-field"]` | The standalone text field. |
| `[data-slot="text-field"]:focus-visible` | A focused text field, showing its focus outline. |
| `[data-slot="text-field"][aria-invalid="true"]` | A text field in its validation-failure state. |
| `[data-slot="text-field"]:disabled` | A locked, non-interactive text field. |

## Accessibility

**Labeled, validated, keyboard-friendly.** Renders as a native `<input>` with full keyboard support, surfaces validation via aria-invalid, and keeps the focus outline visible in both themes. Pair each control with a label element for screen readers.

### Keyboard

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Tab | Move focus to the next focusable control. |
| Shift + Tab | Move focus to the previous focusable control. |
| Enter | Submit the surrounding form, if any. |

